<section class="ftco-section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12 d-flex align-self-stretch ftco-animate">
                <div class="media block-6 d-flex services p-3 py-4 d-block">
                    <div class="icon d-flex mb-3"><span class="flaticon-charity"></span></div>
                    <div class="media-body pl-4">
                        <h2 class="mb-4">What We Do</h2>
                        <h4 style="color:coral">Skills Acquisition for Women and Girls Program</h4>
                        <p style="font-size:larger">
							This program is for empowering women and girls through skills acquisition and training. It is to promote economic development and independence among women and girls.

						</p>
                        <h4 style="color:coral">Guidance and Counseling for Girls Program</h4>
						<p style="font-size:larger">
							This program is meticulously designed and structured to guide our young girls on issues that are important for their lives. Issues such as guarding one’s chastity, open and honest communication, forbearing in difficult times, patience and forbearance, confidence building etc. The program is to empower girls to unlock their full potential, nurture aspirations and become catalyst for positive cultural and economic transformation within their communities and spheres of influence.

						</p>
                        <h4 style="color:coral">Home Economics Program</h4>
                        <p style="font-size:larger">
							Girls are taught the art of home management, and the strategies to overcome poverty and build their analytical and decision-making skills.
						</p>
                        <h4 class="active" style="color:coral">Publicity Campaign Program</h4>
                        <p style="font-size:larger">
							Through weekly radio program WEEGCI educate wider listeners on the importance of standing up to fight poverty and be economically independent. Through questions and answers session WEEGCI listens and registers the fears, barriers, concerns and inadequacies of girls in standing up for themselves.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
